'''Garfield Reeves-Stevens''' is an author who, along with his wife and co-author [[Judith Reeves-Stevens]], penned two ''[[Star Wars]]'' short stories in the 1990s. They wrote "[[One Last Night in the Mos Eisley Cantina: The Tale of the Wolfman and the Lamproid]]" for ''[[Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina]]'' and "[[A Bad Feeling: The Tale of EV-9D9]]" for ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]''. Outside of ''Star Wars'', they are well-known for authoring a bevy of books in the [[Wikipedia:Star Trek|''Star Trek'']] franchise, including a [[w:c:memory-alpha:Star_Trek:_The_Original_Series_(Pocket)#Shatnerverse|series]] co-written by [[Wikipedia:William Shatner|William Shatner]].

